22.17:
But your eyes and your heart are greedy for gain,
    for shedding innocent blood,
    for oppression, and committing violence.

31.34:
No longer will each one teach his neighbor,
or each one teach his brother, saying, “Know the Lord,”
because they will all know me,
from the least of them to the greatest, declares the Lord,
for I will forgive their guilt,
and I will remember their sins no more.
